\doxysubsection{Detailed Description}
a class wrapping capture settings. \mbox{\hyperlink{classins__camera_1_1_capture_settings}{Capture\+Settings}} holds the temperary settings value you want to apply to the camera. The exactly settings to be applied are implied by a list of Setting\+Type,which you may get by calling \mbox{\hyperlink{classins__camera_1_1_capture_settings_af9d0f8729729397f1ccbf3e9c695c7ba}{Get\+Setting\+Types()}}. The types will be automatically recorded when you call any Set\+X\+X\+X() function. However, you can also \mbox{\hyperlink{classins__camera_1_1_capture_settings_a616bbf04ef75dfbcda06510ccfb6cad1}{Reset\+Setting\+Types()}} or \mbox{\hyperlink{classins__camera_1_1_capture_settings_ae169c6442a59b362879ebe5c7d9ea47f}{Update\+Setting\+Types()}} mannually. 

\hypertarget{classins__camera_1_1_capture_settings_autotoc_md0}{}\doxysubsubsection{available settings and value range\+:}\label{classins__camera_1_1_capture_settings_autotoc_md0}

\begin{DoxyItemize}
\item Contrast\+: 0$\sim$256, default 64
\item Saturation\+:0$\sim$256, default 64
\item Brightness\+:-\/256$\sim$256, default 0
\item White\+Balance\+: see \#\+Photography\+Options\+\_\+\+White\+Balance
\item Sharpness\+: 0$\sim$6, default 3 
\end{DoxyItemize}

